    {
        "content": "<p>I think the standard C implementation (<code>std::getline</code> or <code>fgets</code>) only treats <code>\\n</code> as linebreak, and actually will put <code>\\n</code> into the returned string. So on Windows you'll get an extra <code>\\r</code> in the return value, but this is OK.</p>",
